  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a large tagine or Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly browned, about 8 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic and ginger and cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.",
    "Add the lamb and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the broth, beer, cumin, coriander, paprika, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper, and stir to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then cover the tagine and transfer it to the preheated oven.",
    "Bake for 2 hours, or until the lamb is tender and the sauce has thickened.",
    "Stir in the prunes and parsley, and cook for an additional 10 minutes.",
    "Serve the tagine over crusty bread.",
    "Garnish with additional parsley, if desired."
  ],
